{
  "page": "House Donnerly",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <p>This article is about content invented for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(2012_video_game)\" title=\"Game of Thrones (2012 video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> RPG video game developed by Cyanide Studio. Although this is a licensed derivative work based upon <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>, it is not written by him.</p>\n<p>The material on this page should <i>not</i> be considered canonical for the novels, and is provided for informational purposes only.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Donnerly</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"><div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Overlord</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Donnerly</b> is a noble house from the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They have thus far only been mentioned in the video game <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Donnerly_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">House Donnerly at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Donnerly&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Donnerly at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Donnerlys during the timespan of the events described in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>no member has appeared yet.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Game_of_Thrones\"><i>Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Donnerly&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Donnerlys appearing in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Godric_Donnerly\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Godric Donnerly\">Godric Donnerly</a>, a knight of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Arryn\" title=\"Jon Arryn\">Jon Arryn</a>'s household in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.</li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Uthor_Donnerly\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Uthor Donnerly\">Uthor Donnerly</a>, a knight of Lord Jon Arryn's household in King's Landing.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Donnerly&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_(video_game)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Game of Thrones (video game)\">Game of Thrones</a></i></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403191556\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.053 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.211 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 306/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 1866/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3806/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 529/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 6/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 306/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.140/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.43 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  203.253      1 -total\n 98.15%  199.502      1 Template:Noble_House\n 97.79%  198.763      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.68%   23.736     10 Template:Infobox_value\n  3.47%    7.060      2 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.79%    1.598      1 Template:Game\n  0.62%    1.260      1 Template:References\n  0.52%    1.054      1 Template:Mbox\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awo